						               													<description>Hunt monsters, take their parts, forge equipment, brew potions, and battle for glory! Play our story and then build your own!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Legends of Rakasa consists of two base games (Fordra and Monsir), two Legendary Expansions for each base game, and the Alchemy Expansion. each base game comes with enough components to play 1-4 players. Adding players is no problem with no real player cap. Each base game comes with two lands and two road, each land can increase player count by two. 8 to 16 player games is not unheard of with this game. Players can play competitively or cooperatively.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players start in the village with very basic bone equipment they must venture out to the roads and lands to battle monsters, collect spoils, use those spoils to upgrade their equipment so they can take on more challenging monsters, and ultimately striving to achieve the game objective. Players may also use market utilities items and Potion materials to assist them in their battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rakasa was designed to be a vary versatile game where players may choose to play set objectives and game setup rules or design there own. The game is made up and played on individual land and road tiles with decks of cards for each. This system allows players to adjust their games to fit their interests or preferences.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;the base games are set in the Land of Rakasa during the Life Crossing festival. Each year the people of this land celebrate the renewal of life and battle to prove their skills as a hunter. This is done by crafting stronger equipment and defeating the dragons found in each of the lands. Once hunters have proved themselves they can participate in the Mahakasa hunt which is the strongest and most ferocious monster in Rakasa. Hunters who gain parts or trophies from this creature earn the title of Hunter-Warrior, the highest title bestowed to people in the village.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
